## 1. Simple Semantic Search vs. Hybrid Retrieval

| Aspect             | Simple Semantic (Dense)                                              | Hybrid (Dense + Keyword)                                                  |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Strengths**      | Captures meaning beyond exact words, robust to paraphrasing          | Balances semantic meaning with exact matches; better for rare terms/names |
| **Weaknesses**     | Misses rare terms/numbers; risk of irrelevant but “similar” passages | More complex infra (vector DB + inverted index); higher latency           |
| **Infrastructure** | Vector database (ANN search)                                         | Vector DB + traditional search index                                      |
| **Latency**        | Lower (fewer steps)                                                  | Higher (needs fusion/reranking)                                           |
| **Best for**       | General Q\&A, consumer chatbots                                      | Technical/legal/code retrieval, enterprise systems                        |

