## 2. Chunking Strategies

| Chunking Style                | Pros                         | Cons                                                   | Use Case                               |
| ----------------------------- | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------- |
| **Long (1k–2k tokens)**       | Keeps context, fewer splits  | Embeddings blur detail; may retrieve irrelevant extras | Research papers, narrative docs        |
| **Short (100–300 tokens)**    | Precise retrieval            | Loses context, may need multiple hops                  | APIs, legal contracts, code            |
| **Overlapping**               | Handles boundary issues      | Larger index, more storage/query cost                  | Any domain where queries span sections |
| **Semantic/structure-based**  | Aligns with natural sections | Harder to automate                                     | Documents with headings, FAQs, papers  |
| **Adaptive (dynamic sizing)** | Optimizes per domain         | More engineering effort                                | Multi-domain platforms                 |

