## 4. Retrieval Accuracy vs. Latency (How Platforms Balance)

| Stage              | Purpose                                                 | Typical Size   | Latency Budget    |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- | -------------- | ----------------- |
| **Initial Recall** | Fast candidate retrieval                                | Top-100 to 200 | <50ms             |
| **Reranking**      | Apply more accurate models (cross-encoders, small LLMs) | Top-20         | 100–300ms         |
| **Fusion**         | Merge dense + keyword hits                              | —              | Small overhead    |
| **Caching**        | Serve frequent queries instantly                        | —              | Near-zero         |
| **Overall Goal**   | Sub-second response (consumer) or <2s (enterprise)      | —              | 200–400ms typical |

